Task: Write tests for keyboard input translation + Implement keyboard input handling
Phase: 4 - Keyboard Input Pipeline

Summary:
Created input/mod.rs translating winit KeyEvents to terminal byte sequences.
Red phase: 39 tests (all failing with todo!()).
Green phase: Implemented translate_key(), ctrl_key_byte(), named_key_bytes().

Files created/modified:
- src/input/mod.rs (NEW): Key translation, 39 tests
- src/lib.rs: Added input submodule

Key design decisions:
- translate_key() takes logical_key, text, state, modifiers as separate params (not full KeyEvent)
  to keep the module testable without constructing winit event structs
- Ctrl+letter: convert to control byte (0x01..0x1A) via ctrl_key_byte()
- Named keys dispatched through named_key_bytes() with complete mapping
- F1-F4 use SS3 format (\x1bOP..S), F5-F12 use CSI ~ format
- Arrow keys use normal mode CSI sequences (not application cursor mode)
- Key releases and modifier-only presses filtered to None
